quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  7,88,"The arrogant leaders of his people said, \"Shu'ayb, we will expel you and your fellow believers from our town unless you return to our faith.\" He said, \"Even though we detest it"
  7,89,"We would be inventing lies against God if we returned to your faith after God has delivered us from it. It is not for us to return to it unless God our Lord so willed. Our Lord encompasses all things in His knowledge. We have put our trust in God. Our Lord, expose the truth [and judge] between us and our people, You are the best judge"
  7,90,"The leading men of his people who were bent on denying the truth, said, \"If you follow Shu'ayb, you will certainly be the losers"
  7,91,Thereupon an earthquake overtook them and morning found them lying flattened in their homes
  7,92,"those who had denied Shu'ayb became as though they had never lived there. Those who denied Shu'ayb, were themselves the losers"
  7,93,"So he turned away from them, saying, \"My people, I delivered my Lord's messages to you and gave you sincere advice, so why should I grieve for people who refused to believe"
  7,94,"Whenever We sent a prophet to a town, We afflicted its people with suffering and adversity, so that they might humble themselves [before God]"
  7,95,"and then We changed their hardship into ease until they grew affluent and said, \"Our fathers had also experienced adversity and prosperity,\" then We seized them suddenly, unawares"
  7,96,"Had the people of those towns believed in and feared God, We would have showered upon them blessings from heaven and earth, but they rejected the truth. So We seized them on account of their misdeeds"
  7,97,Do the people of these towns now feel secure against the coming of Our punishment upon them by night while they are asleep
  7,98,"Or, do they feel secure against the coming of Our punishment upon them in the forenoon while they are at play"
  7,99,Do they feel secure against God's devising? No one feels secure against God's devising except for those doomed to ruin
  7,100,Does it not guide the people who inherit the land from former people that We can punish them for their sins if We will? And seal up their hearts so that they would not be able to lend an ear to words of guidance
  7,101,"We have told you the stories of those towns: their messengers came to them with clear signs, but they were never going to believe in something they had already rejected. Thus God seals up the hearts of those who deny the truth"
  7,102,"We found most of them untrue to their covenants, indeed We found most of them to be defiant"
  7,103,After them We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs. But they willfully rejected them. Consider the end of the evil-doers
  7,104,"Moses said, \"Pharaoh, I am a messenger from the Lord of the Universe"
  7,105,"duty-bound to say nothing about God but the truth, and I have brought you a clear sign from your Lord. Let the Children of Israel go with me"
  7,106,"[Pharaoh] said, \"If you come with a sign, then produce it, if you are telling the truth"
  7,107,"Then Moses threw down his staff and suddenly, unmistakably, it appeared as a serpent"
  7,108,"and he drew forth his hand, and it appeared [shining] white to the beholders"
  7,109,"The chiefs of Pharaoh's people said, \"This is most surely a skillful magician"
  7,110,"who seeks to drive you from your land!\" Pharaoh said, \"What then do you advise"
  7,111,"They said, \"Let him and his brother wait awhile, and send into the cities summoners"
  7,112,who should bring to you every skillful magician
  7,113,"And the magicians came to Pharaoh and asked, \"Shall we have a reward, if we should prevail"
  7,114,"Pharaoh replied, \"Certainly, and you shall also become my courtiers"
  7,115,"They said, \"Moses, will you first throw, or shall we"
  7,116,"He said, \"You throw [first]!\" When they made their cast, they bewitched the eyes of the people and struck them with awe, for they showed a great [feat of] magic"